# Visualization — generic across every system (view, sim, teleop, auto). Any ROS
# graph topics feed two interchangeable clients: foxglove_bridge serves a browser
# over a websocket (headless, remote); rviz2 renders locally (needs an X display).
# Launched separately from the system it watches. Nodes are plum boxes, topics
# cream pills.
...@styles
direction: right

topics: /topics { class: topic }

bridge: foxglove_bridge { class: node }
rviz: rviz2 { class: node }
studio: Foxglove Studio { class: node }
window: RViz { class: node }

topics -> bridge
topics -> rviz
bridge -> studio: ws://8765
rviz -> window: X display
